Subject: Re: Deutsche Post Security Cup 2013



IMHO the goal here is not to find many vulns, it is to find none and
therefore "prove" that the product is secure. The E-POST product is
highly questioned in Germany, because it is sold as secure encrypted
email service, although the security is only between server and client.
The server unencrypts the mail and virus checks it or whatever else. I
think I don't need to comment any further, just corelate those two
facts. 

Alexander Georgiev 

